body:
So I recently moved from my home in South Texas to my new apartment in more Central Texas (what I assume is closer to the server home since It's further North). I bought a new router (the modem was included with the apartment) which is an upgrade from the one I have at my home and am the only one in the apartment (the only one using my wifi) and yet my ping way worse then back home. 

Back home I'd run an average of about 60 ping whereas my new average is roughly 3000. I'm 6-7 feet from the router and the only one using my wifi (which is on a 600Mbps-1.3Gbps network AND I'm closer to where the servers are located.

_**What the hell**_{{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}}
